name: Monarka Novum
description: “Part of the biggest migration event on the cosmos, this specimen travels from both corners of the Milk Way in a multi generation cosmic event, sometimes the swarm can me spotted by telescope as a big scintillant meteor” | This is a digitally developed art. Originally painted on its negative colors on paper using watercolor technique. This limited edition of the reveled piece is 3336x3192 px, 5.1MB, painted in 140lb cold pressed cotton paper by Adilson Matioli.
